  "description": "<p><u><strong>Roles & Responsibilities</strong></u></p><p></p><ul><li>To conduct Phonics classes in small group setting</li><li>Engage and motive students in their learning process</li><li>Proactively communicate with the parents on their child(ren) learning progress</li><li>Other duties as assigned by immediate supervisor</li></ul><p><u><strong>Requirements</strong></u></p><ul><li>Minimum Diploma Holder </li><li>Passionate in teaching and enjoy working with children</li><li>Able to communicate in English and Mandarin to parents</li><li>Team Player</li><li>Able to work on weekdays evenings and weekends</li><li>No prior experience is required</li></ul>",
